examples.en: He said something that really bothered me.
It really bothered me that he'd forgotten my birthday.
She is bothered by family problems.
I feel bla, I don't want to be bothered by anybody.
Has anyone bothered to find out how much all this is going to cost?
It was so hot I couldn't be bothered to cook.
'What film do you want to see?' 'I'm not bothered.'
The mere thought of her bothered him and made his heart beat faster.
They weren't bothered  in fact they were killing themselves laughing.
Alexander Hamilton appears to have been bothered by the fact that he was a bastard child.
Our lassitude was such that we couldn't even be bothered to get more soda from the fridge.
They don't seem to be greatly bothered by the delay.
The slightest dislocation in her daily routine bothered the elderly woman.
